                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.1D1/35: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-11T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 11, 1929—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>120. Your 33, April 11, noon.<note n="8" xml:id="d239fn8">Not printed.</note> You
                    are requested to notify the Secretary General of the League of Nations in the
                    sense of the following, referring to his communication of April 10, 1929,
                    addressed to the Secretary of State: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>The Government of the United States, being desirous of cooperating in a
                            work which has for its object the proper treatment of foreigners, is
                            pleased to inform the Secretary General that it has designated George A.
                            Gordon, American First Secretary at Paris, to attend the Conference as a
                            technical expert to cooperate in a consultative capacity.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Please request Consul at Geneva to forward immediately to Gordon League documents
                    concerning the Conference including the draft Convention and any information
                    which he believes will be of assistance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
